# 24 bit version of ANSI-color
# |------------+-----------+-----------+---------+-------------+------------------------------------------+-----------------|------------+-----------+-----------+---------+-------------+------------------------------------------+-----------------|
# | foreground | octal     | hex       | bash    | description | example                                  | NOTE            | background | octal     | hex       | bash    | description | example                                  | NOTE            |
# |------------+-----------+-----------+---------+-------------+------------------------------------------+-----------------|------------+-----------+-----------+---------+-------------+------------------------------------------+-----------------|
# |      0-255 | \033[38;2 | \x1b[38;2 | \e[38;2 | R = red     | echo -e '\033[38;2;255;0;02m####\033[m'  | R=255, G=0, B=0 |      0-255 | \033[48;2 | \x1b[48;2 | \e[48;2 | R = red     | echo -e '\033[48;2;255;0;02m####\033[m'  | R=255, G=0, B=0 |
# |      0-255 | \033[38;2 | \x1b[38;2 | \e[38;2 | G = green   | echo -e '\033[38;2;;0;255;02m####\033[m' | R=0, G=255, B=0 |      0-255 | \033[48;2 | \x1b[48;2 | \e[48;2 | G = green   | echo -e '\033[48;2;;0;255;02m####\033[m' | R=0, G=255, B=0 |
# |      0-255 | \033[38;2 | \x1b[38;2 | \e[38;2 | B = blue    | echo -e '\033[38;2;0;0;2552m####\033[m'  | R=0, G=0, B=255 |      0-255 | \033[48;2 | \x1b[48;2 | \e[48;2 | B = blue    | echo -e '\033[48;2;0;0;2552m####\033[m'  | R=0, G=0, B=255 |
